          "By the 2010s, the limitations of human-in-the-loop systems became apparent [4]. Targets moved faster than human decision-makers could track them. Opportunities for engagement disappeared in the time it took to obtain human approval. Military strategists recognized that speed was the decisive factor in modern warfare. The solution was to introduce AI systems that could identify and track targets autonomously, accelerating the kill chain from hours to minutes [2].",
